# TUI Testing & QA Pipeline
# Comprehensive testing for Textual-based UI
#
# Challenge: TUIs harder to test than web UIs (no browser automation)
# Solution: Textual's built-in snapshot testing + manual QA
#
# Flow:
# 1. create_snapshots: Generate reference screenshots for all screens
# 2. Parallel testing:
#    - run_unit_tests: Widget behavior, event handlers
#    - run_snapshot_tests: Visual regression testing
#    - run_interaction_tests: Keyboard navigation, mouse clicks
#    - run_accessibility_tests: Screen reader compatibility
# 3. manual_qa: Human testing on different terminals (iTerm, Windows Terminal, etc.)
# 4. performance_profiling: Frame time analysis, memory leaks
# 5. generate_report: Test coverage + performance metrics
#
# Ensures: Consistent behavior across terminal emulators

generate_report ∘ performance_profiling ∘ manual_qa ∘ (run_unit_tests × run_snapshot_tests × run_interaction_tests × run_accessibility_tests) ∘ create_snapshots
